[{"location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Modules","page":"API","title":"Modules","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Modules = [Moma.Categories, Moma.TrafficNetwork]\nOrder = [:module]","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Moma.Categories","page":"API","title":"Moma.Categories","text":"module Categories\n\nThis module provides basic categorical constructions used in Memory Evolutive Systems (MES). It includes implementations of objects, morphisms, categories, functors, natural transformations, and patterns, along with functions for working with these constructions.\n\nExports\n\nObject: Represents an object in a category\nMorphism: Represents a morphism between objects\nCategory: Represents a category with objects and morphisms\nFunctor: Represents a functor between categories\nNaturalTransformation: Represents a natural transformation between functors\nPattern: Represents a pattern (diagram) in a category\nidentity: Creates an identity morphism for an object\ncompose: Composes two morphisms\ncreate_pattern: Creates a pattern from objects and morphisms\ncheck_binding: Checks if an object forms a colimit for a pattern\nfind_colimit: Finds or constructs colimits for patterns\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"api/#Moma.TrafficNetwork","page":"API","title":"Moma.TrafficNetwork","text":"Module implementing a traffic network example using Memory Evolutive Systems.\n\nThis module provides an example implementation of Memory Evolutive Systems (MES) using traffic networks. It demonstrates how to model and analyze traffic flow using categorical constructions.\n\nExports\n\nRoadSegment: Represents a road segment in the traffic network\nJunction: Represents a junction connecting road segments\ncreate_traffic_network: Creates a traffic network with road segments and junctions\nanalyze_traffic_flow: Analyzes traffic flow in the network\n\nThe module shows how to:\n\nModel road segments and junctions as objects in a category\nRepresent traffic flow using morphisms\nAnalyze network properties using categorical constructions\nTrack network state evolution over time\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"api/#Categories","page":"API","title":"Categories","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Types","page":"API","title":"Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Moma.Categories.Object\nMoma.Categories.Morphism\nMoma.Categories.Category\nMoma.Categories.Functor\nMoma.Categories.NaturalTransformation\nMoma.Categories.Pattern","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Moma.Categories.Object","page":"API","title":"Moma.Categories.Object","text":"Object{T}\n\nRepresents an object in a category.\n\nFields\n\nid::Symbol: Unique identifier for the object\ndata::T: Data associated with the object\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#Moma.Categories.Morphism","page":"API","title":"Moma.Categories.Morphism","text":"Morphism{S,T}\n\nRepresents a morphism between objects in a category.\n\nFields\n\nsource::Object{S}: Source object\ntarget::Object{T}: Target object\nmap::Function: Function mapping source to target\nid::Symbol: Unique identifier for the morphism\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#Moma.Categories.Category","page":"API","title":"Moma.Categories.Category","text":"Category\n\nRepresents a category with objects and morphisms.\n\nFields\n\nobjects::Vector{<:Object}: Objects in the category\nmorphisms::Vector{<:Morphism}: Morphisms in the category\nid::Symbol: Unique identifier for the category\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#Moma.Categories.Functor","page":"API","title":"Moma.Categories.Functor","text":"Functor\n\nRepresents a functor between categories.\n\nFields\n\nsource::Category: Source category\ntarget::Category: Target category\nobject_map::Dict{<:Object,<:Object}: Mapping of objects\nmorphism_map::Dict{<:Morphism,<:Morphism}: Mapping of morphisms\nid::Symbol: Unique identifier for the functor\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#Moma.Categories.NaturalTransformation","page":"API","title":"Moma.Categories.NaturalTransformation","text":"NaturalTransformation\n\nRepresents a natural transformation between functors.\n\nFields\n\nsource::Functor: Source functor\ntarget::Functor: Target functor\ncomponents::Dict{<:Object,<:Morphism}: Component morphisms\nid::Symbol: Unique identifier for the natural transformation\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#Moma.Categories.Pattern","page":"API","title":"Moma.Categories.Pattern","text":"Pattern\n\nRepresents a pattern (diagram) in a category.\n\nFields\n\ncategory::Category: The category containing the pattern\nobjects::Vector{<:Object}: Objects in the pattern\nmorphisms::Vector{<:Morphism}: Morphisms in the pattern\nid::Symbol: Unique identifier for the pattern\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#Functions","page":"API","title":"Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Moma.Categories.identity\nMoma.Categories.compose\nMoma.Categories.create_pattern\nMoma.Categories.check_binding\nMoma.Categories.find_colimit","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Moma.Categories.identity","page":"API","title":"Moma.Categories.identity","text":"identity(obj::Object)\n\nCreate an identity morphism for an object.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Moma.Categories.compose","page":"API","title":"Moma.Categories.compose","text":"compose(f::Morphism, g::Morphism)\n\nCompose two morphisms if they are composable.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Moma.Categories.create_pattern","page":"API","title":"Moma.Categories.create_pattern","text":"create_pattern(category::Category, objects::Vector{<:Object}, morphisms::Vector{<:Morphism})\n\nCreate a pattern from a subset of objects and morphisms in a category.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Moma.Categories.check_binding","page":"API","title":"Moma.Categories.check_binding","text":"check_binding(object::Object, bindings::Dict{<:Object,<:Morphism}, pattern::Pattern)\n\nCheck if an object with specified bindings forms a colimit for a pattern.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Moma.Categories.find_colimit","page":"API","title":"Moma.Categories.find_colimit","text":"find_colimit(pattern::Pattern)\n\nFind or construct a colimit for a pattern.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Traffic-Network-Example","page":"API","title":"Traffic Network Example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Types-2","page":"API","title":"Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Moma.TrafficNetwork.RoadSegment\nMoma.TrafficNetwork.Junction","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Moma.TrafficNetwork.RoadSegment","page":"API","title":"Moma.TrafficNetwork.RoadSegment","text":"Represents a road segment with traffic data.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#Moma.TrafficNetwork.Junction","page":"API","title":"Moma.TrafficNetwork.Junction","text":"Represents a junction point in the traffic network.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#Functions-2","page":"API","title":"Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Moma.TrafficNetwork.create_traffic_network\nMoma.TrafficNetwork.analyze_traffic_flow","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Moma.TrafficNetwork.create_traffic_network","page":"API","title":"Moma.TrafficNetwork.create_traffic_network","text":"create_traffic_network()\n\nCreate a simple traffic network as a category.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Moma.TrafficNetwork.analyze_traffic_flow","page":"API","title":"Moma.TrafficNetwork.analyze_traffic_flow","text":"analyze_traffic_flow(network::Category)\n\nAnalyze traffic flow patterns in the network using categorical constructions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"mes07/#MES07:-Memory-Evolutive-Systems","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes07/#Overview","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"Overview","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes07/","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"This foundational paper introduces Memory Evolutive Systems (MES) as mathematical models for autonomous evolutionary systems, particularly focusing on biological and social systems, including nervous systems of higher animals. The work is rooted in category theory and represents two decades of research development.","category":"page"},{"location":"mes07/#Key-Concepts","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"Key Concepts","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes07/#Complexity-Characterization","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"Complexity Characterization","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes07/","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"The paper addresses three fundamental problems:","category":"page"},{"location":"mes07/","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"The Binding Problem: How simple objects combine to form a \"whole greater than the sum of its parts\"\nThe Emergence Problem: How properties of complex objects relate to their elementary components\nThe Hierarchy Problem: Explaining the formation of increasingly complex objects, from elementary particles to societies","category":"page"},{"location":"mes07/#Self-Regulation","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"Self-Regulation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes07/","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"The paper introduces key characteristics that allow for autonomy through self-regulation:","category":"page"},{"location":"mes07/","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"Internal regulation systems\nCapacity to recognize environmental characteristics\nDevelopment of appropriate responses\nIntroduction of co-regulators (CR) for different hierarchy levels\nFlexible memory systems for adaptation","category":"page"},{"location":"mes07/#Cognitive-Systems","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"Cognitive Systems","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes07/","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"The paper explores applications to:","category":"page"},{"location":"mes07/","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"Nervous system modeling\nCognition processes\nConsciousness modeling\nDevelopment of personal memory (archetypal core)","category":"page"},{"location":"mes07/#Mathematical-Framework","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"Mathematical Framework","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes07/","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"The model uses:","category":"page"},{"location":"mes07/","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"Category theory as the foundational mathematical structure\nComplex systems theory\nHierarchical evolutive systems based on colimit concepts\nNetwork theory for co-regulator interactions","category":"page"},{"location":"mes07/#Applications","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"Applications","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes07/","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"The framework has applications in:","category":"page"},{"location":"mes07/","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"Biology\nMedicine\nSociology\nEcology\nEconomics\nComplex systems analysis","category":"page"},{"location":"mes07/#Historical-Context","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"Historical Context","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes07/","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"The work emerged from a collaboration between:","category":"page"},{"location":"mes07/","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"Jean-Paul Vanbremeersch (physician specializing in gerontology)\nAndrÃ©e C. Ehresmann (mathematician)","category":"page"},{"location":"mes07/","page":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"Their collaboration began in 1980, leading to the development of MES theory. ","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/#MES25:-A-Mathematical-Framework-for-Enriching-Human-Machine-Interactions","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: A Mathematical Framework for Enriching Human-Machine Interactions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes25/#Overview","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"Overview","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"This paper presents a conceptual mathematical framework for developing rich human-machine interactions to improve decision-making in social organizations. It introduces the concept of a \"multi-level artificial cognitive system\" called a data analyser (DA) that collaborates with humans in data analysis and decision-making processes.","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/#Key-Concepts","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"Key Concepts","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes25/#Data-Analyser-(DA)","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"Data Analyser (DA)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"The DA is designed to:","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"Collect and analyze data\nLearn and develop autonomous procedures\nAnticipate situations\nDevelop new responses\nImprove decision-making processes","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/#Human-Machine-Partnership","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"Human-Machine Partnership","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"The framework focuses on:","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"Collaborative data analysis\nKnowledge extension\nAutonomous learning\nCreation of new procedures\nDeep anticipation capabilities","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/#Memory-Evolutive-Systems-Integration","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"Memory Evolutive Systems Integration","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"The paper uses MES to describe:","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"Social organization operations\nDA construction and evolution\nMulti-scale system interactions\nMulti-agent coordination\nMulti-temporality handling","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/#Technical-Framework","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"Technical Framework","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes25/#AI-Integration","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"AI Integration","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"The paper discusses:","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"Historical AI development\nSymbolic AI approaches\nConnectionist paradigms\nIntegration of multiple AI paradigms\nCategory theory applications","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/#Implementation-Aspects","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"Implementation Aspects","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"Key implementation features:","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"Multi-level cognitive systems\nRich human-machine interactions\nAnticipatory capabilities\nRisk prevention strategies\nOpportunity identification","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/#Applications","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"Applications","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes25/#Healthcare-Example","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"Healthcare Example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"Demonstrates DA implementation in:","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"Symptom detection\nAutonomous response selection\nDecision-making participation\nCommunication improvement\nMisunderstanding detection","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/#General-Applications","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"General Applications","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"The framework can be applied to:","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"Social organizations\nHealthcare institutions\nEducational systems\nBusiness environments\nComplex decision-making scenarios","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/#Future-Directions","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"Future Directions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"The paper suggests development paths for:","category":"page"},{"location":"mes25/","page":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"Third-generation AI systems\nEnhanced human-machine collaboration\nImproved anticipatory capabilities\nRisk prevention mechanisms\nDecision-making optimization ","category":"page"},{"location":"#Moma.jl-Documentation","page":"Home","title":"Moma.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Welcome to the documentation for Moma.jl, a Julia package implementing Memory Evolutive Systems (MES) for complex system modeling and analysis.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Overview","page":"Home","title":"Overview","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Moma.jl provides tools for working with Memory Evolutive Systems, a mathematical framework for modeling complex hierarchical systems that evolve over time. The package includes implementations of categorical constructions and practical examples like traffic network analysis.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"To install Moma.jl, use Julia's package manager:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(\"Moma\")","category":"page"},{"location":"#Basic-Usage","page":"Home","title":"Basic Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Here's a simple example of creating and analyzing a traffic network:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Moma\n\n# Create a traffic network\nnetwork = create_traffic_network()\n\n# Analyze traffic flow\nresults = analyze_traffic_flow(network)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Package-Structure","page":"Home","title":"Package Structure","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The package consists of two main modules:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Categories: Implements basic categorical constructions used in MES\nTrafficNetwork: Provides an example implementation using traffic networks","category":"page"},{"location":"#Features","page":"Home","title":"Features","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Categorical-Constructions","page":"Home","title":"Categorical Constructions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Objects and morphisms in categories\nFunctors and natural transformations\nPattern matching and colimit finding","category":"page"},{"location":"#Traffic-Network-Example","page":"Home","title":"Traffic Network Example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Road segment and junction modeling\nTraffic flow analysis\nNetwork state evolution","category":"page"},{"location":"#Contributing","page":"Home","title":"Contributing","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Contributions to Moma.jl are welcome! Please feel free to submit issues and pull requests on our GitHub repository. ","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/#MOMA25:-Monetary-Macro-Accounting-Theory","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting Theory","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/#Overview","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"Overview","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"This paper develops a specification for software for macro accounting (MoMa) and a monetary macro accounting theory (MoMaT). It presents a novel approach where money functions as a medium of payment for obligations and debts, rather than just a medium of exchange.","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/#Key-Concepts","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"Key Concepts","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/#Theoretical-Framework","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"Theoretical Framework","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"The paper addresses:","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"Temporal misalignment in production\nLegal principles of Separation and Abstraction\nDebt, contracts, and property rights\nMulti-level monetary systems analysis","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/#System-Levels","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"System Levels","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"The monetary system operates at three interconnected levels:","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"Micro Level: Division of labor facilitation\nMeso Level: Risk sharing in banking\nMacro Level: GDP distribution through issued money","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/#Core-Components","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"Core Components","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/#Bill-of-Exchange-(BoE)","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"Bill of Exchange (BoE)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"Serves as:","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"Unifying instrument\nBridge between debt processes\nMoney issuing mechanism\nConnection between fiat and gold-based systems","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/#Mathematical-Foundations","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"Mathematical Foundations","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"Utilizes:","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"Sheaf theory for accounting invariances\nHomology theory for monetary policy\nOpen Games for computation\nMulti-agent model analysis","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/#Applications","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"Applications","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/#Supply-Chain-Finance","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"Supply Chain Finance","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"Debt networks analysis\nPayment systems integration\nRisk distribution mechanisms\nFinancial obligation tracking","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/#Monetary-Policy","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"Monetary Policy","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"Central banking operations\nMoney circulation analysis\nDebt vortices study\nFinancial obligation resolution","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/#Technical-Implementation","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"Technical Implementation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/#Software-Components","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"Software Components","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"MoMa implementation includes:","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"Macro accounting systems\nSmart contracts\nStructural econometric models\nData analysis tools","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/#Mathematical-Tools","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"Mathematical Tools","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"Employs:","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"Category theory\nSheaf theory\nHomology theory\nGame theory","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/#Future-Implications","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"Future Implications","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"The framework provides foundations for:","category":"page"},{"location":"moma25/","page":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"Modern monetary systems\nDigital currency development\nFinancial system evolution\nEconomic policy making ","category":"page"},{"location":"papers/#Papers","page":"Overview","title":"Papers","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"papers/","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"This section provides summaries of the key papers that form the foundation of the Moma package. Each paper is detailed on its own page, accessible through the links below.","category":"page"},{"location":"papers/#[MES07:-Memory-Evolutive-Systems](mes07.md)","page":"Overview","title":"MES07: Memory Evolutive Systems","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"papers/","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"Title: \"Memory Evolutive Systems: An Overview of Concepts and Methodologies\"","category":"page"},{"location":"papers/","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"A foundational paper introducing Memory Evolutive Systems (MES) as mathematical models for autonomous evolutionary systems. This work establishes the core theoretical framework used throughout the Moma package.","category":"page"},{"location":"papers/","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"Read more about MES07...","category":"page"},{"location":"papers/#[MES25:-Human-Machine-Interactions](mes25.md)","page":"Overview","title":"MES25: Human-Machine Interactions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"papers/","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"Title: \"A Mathematical Framework for Enriching Human-Machine Interactions\"","category":"page"},{"location":"papers/","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"Building upon MES07, this paper presents a framework for developing rich human-machine interactions in social organizations, introducing the concept of a data analyser (DA) for improved decision-making.","category":"page"},{"location":"papers/","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"Read more about MES25...","category":"page"},{"location":"papers/#[MOMA25:-Monetary-Macro-Accounting](moma25.md)","page":"Overview","title":"MOMA25: Monetary Macro Accounting","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"papers/","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"Title: \"Monetary Macro Accounting Theory\"","category":"page"},{"location":"papers/","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"The latest paper introduces the MoMa framework for monetary macro accounting, presenting a novel approach to understanding money as a medium of payment for obligations and debts.","category":"page"},{"location":"papers/","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"Read more about MOMA25...","category":"page"},{"location":"papers/#Implementation-in-Moma.jl","page":"Overview","title":"Implementation in Moma.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"papers/","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"The Moma.jl package implements the methodologies and frameworks described in these papers, integrating:","category":"page"},{"location":"papers/","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"Memory evolutive systems from MES07\nHuman-machine interaction frameworks from MES25\nMonetary macro accounting concepts from MOMA25","category":"page"},{"location":"papers/","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"For detailed implementation examples, see the API Reference. ","category":"page"}]
